description:
in this economy it's back to basics.  nothing like a big-ass burger for dinner - was here last week with friends Matt and Sonny.  if you are low on your bad cholesterols, there is no better way to rebalance than having a Pearl's special, a milkshake and some garlic fries.  the meat was good, and the service was great.  my only concern is that i doubt  there was really a half pound of beef in there.  if i'm shoveling fat into my veins at the very least i'd like to regulate the prescription.  Probably enough room in the restaurant for about ten people so it's a good place to get takeout.

Pearl's will fit nicely into any evening's equation (refuse to use the phrase "pearls of wisdom").  You don't even have to leave the immediate area.  For eg...

* Not enough $ for the good stuff at Fleur De Lys?  supplement with Pearl's;
* Expensive nite at the theater? go to Pearl's for dinner - not sure how this would affect your date;
* Drinking and Dancing?  Pearl's for dinner followed by Ambassador, Clift Hotel and / or Ruby Skye;
* Exhausted after defending your TL drug territory and dealing with non-paying customers, errant prostitutes and the cops? re-load at Pearl's.

yes the burgers are good.  i can't believe i've lived in San Francisco for most of my life and have never been here until now.
